# .lycheeignore — External URLs excluded from lychee link checking
#
# Entries here are URLs that are known-dead, rate-limited, or
# legitimately inaccessible. Each entry is documented with a reason.
#
# Format: one URL/pattern per line. Lychee supports glob-style patterns.

# Anthropic article URL — moved/redirected after site restructure.
# Content archived in docs/research/sources/ via fetch_source.py.
https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/claude-research-system

# Heavybit DevRel article — 404; content not cached locally.
# Noted in docs/research/comms-marketing-bizdev.md as "not cached".
https://www.heavybit.com/library/article/dev-rel-vs-developer-marketing

# Steve McConnell — team topologies article; 404.
# Noted in docs/research/pm-and-team-structures.md as "HTTP 404".
https://stevemcconnell.com/articles/software-development-team-topologies/

# Martinfowler ADR article — HTTP 404 at time of research (2026-03-06).
# Noted in docs/research/pm-and-team-structures.md as "HTTP 404;
# supplemented by domain expertise".
https://www.martinfowler.com/articles/adr.html

# Atlassian kanban-vs-scrum — returns HTTP 202 Accepted instead of 200.
# Lychee treats non-200 responses (e.g., 202 Accepted) as failures; content is valid and accessible.
https://www.atlassian.com/agile/kanban/kanban-vs-scrum

# conventionalcommits.org — intermittent network errors from GitHub Actions
# runners (connection refused / DNS failure). Site is live; referenced in
# CONTRIBUTING.md (bare domain) and docs/research/dev-workflow-automations.md
# (/en/v1.0.0/ path). Both variants excluded.
https://www.conventionalcommits.org/
https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/

# istio.io traffic-management — network errors from GitHub Actions runners
# (connection refused / DNS failure). Istio site is live and accessible;
# referenced in docs/research/six-layer-topological-extension.md.
# May be due to firewall/proxy rules in GitHub's CI environment.
https://istio.io/latest/docs/concepts/traffic-management/

# spec.modelcontextprotocol.io — TLS handshake failures from GitHub Actions runners.
# Site is live; referenced in docs/guides/mcp-integration.md.
# CI environment SSL/TLS configuration issue, not a dead link.
https://spec.modelcontextprotocol.io/

# AccessiTech/EndogenAI issue #35 — original repo issue that inspired this project.
# The AccessiTech/EndogenAI repository no longer exists; issue is permanently 404.
# Referenced in README.md as historical context.
https://github.com/AccessiTech/EndogenAI/issues/35

# cicirello/issue-completion-stats — repository no longer exists (404).
# Referenced in docs/research/issue-metrics-action.md as a DEFER candidate.
https://github.com/cicirello/issue-completion-stats

# The Atlantic "As We May Think" (Bush, 1945) returns 503 intermittently from CI runners.
# Canonical historical reference; URL is correct and publicly accessible outside CI.
# Appears in docs/research/endogenic-design-paper.md and sprint-C-h3-augmentive.md.
https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/1945/07/as-we-may-think/303881/
